Package memory

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Allocable
    Object that is manage by an AllocatorOf
    Freeable
    Object that can be freed from memory
    MemoryObject
    MemoryObject is an interface that must be implemented if you want your object to be able to be reused.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AllocatorOf<T extends Allocable>
    AllocatorOf
    Memory Manager.
    Binary  
    Memory
    The class that allocate and manage all objects in memory.
    MemoryPool<E extends MemoryObject>
    The MemoryPool is the structure that contains all objects in the pool of memory. It is implemented using an array to stock the objects, and a stack to stock the indices of free objects, i.e their position in the array.
